The paper focuses on transfer learning for trajectory tracking in robotics, which falls under the category of robotics and control (cs.RO). The paper also utilizes machine learning techniques such as adaptive control and iterative learning control, which are commonly used in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses theoretical control results, which suggests that it may also belong to the subfield of systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper uses a map from desired trajectories to inputs, which is a common technique in the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper uses experimental results with quadrotor platforms, which suggests that it may also belong to the subfield of computer vision (cs.CV).
